Loved it. 
Alot of excellent stores and shopping at Macy's was Great

This historic building is very important for the city of Chicago. This building is the only one, that survived Chicago's great fire in 1871. Now surrounded with chic shopping district and Magnificent Mile, it serves like a tourist destination.
Beautiful building where you can find art and learn about the city.

Really pretty we stayed near the tower for a birthday weekend in my home town chicago. I was hoping to see it at night but chicago weathee had other plans. Some issues trash on the ground and people trying to sell "school candy".
Interesting view over Chicago. One of the important must see attractions in Chicago.

Went there for a Saturday Buffet date with wife and we had a great evening. The place has nicely set up the ambiance for a romantic dinner date  They serve some really good  food, spread was limited but nicely curated. The desert section was my favorite as it had a lot of variety.

Not at all a great place at that price. Nothing great about ambience or food. Small place actually. Staff service is good and courteous. Less staff. You need to go hotel reception to pay your bill. No ice cream in the desert.
Food is good but limited starters in buffet. ambience was good. If you want have some privacy like closed doors environment I would suggest not to choose monsoon

A descent place to dine-in. Courteous staff and good service.

Food - we tried pizza, pasta and desserts. Pizza was very good but pasta disappointed a bit in terms of taste and quality. The raspberry cheesecake was not good but chocolate bomb was unique.
Ambience - average.
Service - very good staff.

It's been quite some time and we were craving for buffet lunch. After looking for multiple options, we found this to be better than others. This buffet was labelled as fit and healthy so we were also excited for some amazing healthy stuff. Since we reached there just when the buffet started so we thought main course items are yet to be kept. To our greatest surprise there was no main course. So the menu comprised of salads and desserts which is so weird and bizarre. The only main course option was cold burger and cold sandwich which was terrible. Except for khao suey soup and couple of salads n desserts, majority of the offerings were average to below average. The most horrific of all was papadi chaat where the ingredients were papadi and dahi, neither it was healthy nor justified to not put basic ingredients. Healthy doesn't mean non inclusion of basic items. With salads which anyways is an indispensable part of the buffet plus umpteen desserts which has nothing to do with healthiness this buffet was the worse ever experience so far. Coming to their service, it was again not even close to what we expected. The serving folks lacked basic skills in regard to everything. The only sigh of relief was the ambience which was surely in line with what we expected. Overall not suggested in any case!!!
We had a large group and enjoyed the island very much while we camped for 5 days!  Paul is the best ranger! Cheers!

We came to the island for a cruise, dinner and performance. The staff on the cruise and the island were all welcoming. The island is beautiful & wonderfully quite. The trip as a whole was wonderful and being caught in a thunderstorm on the way back was mystical!

I like how it is surrounded by water. I just can't get this at any other park. That is why this one is special. I like feeling trapped by natures most vicious element, salt water. You see I'm deathly allergic to water. That's why I don't exist.
You can pay for a boat to take you, or take your own boat. Indian Village on Island on the western Puget Sound. Easy access from the east side of the sound.
Quiet and beautiful park. Camped one night and hiked around the island. Highly recommended.

Was just ok. Was disappointed they didnt even bother to put out any white rice for the lunch buffet and the fried rice was well, overfried. The other items were just barely, meh. For 20 bucks for 2 people, it should have been a lot better. Seemed sloppy.

One of those wonderful hole in the wall treasures. Authentic Mexican food that never disappoints. Staff is friendly and the food is great.
Best Mexican food in Sonoma County!
Great el pastor. Consistently good Mexican food.

Where the locals eat. El Sombrero has been in business for over 30+ years. It is a locally family owned business and the food is great. If you want some good salsa, El Sombrero Is the place. I usually go for the tacos with tripas, chorizo, and a pastor are my favorites. Try it! I would have taken pictures but when I realized, it was too late.
Over 2 decades,where else can you get a tongue burrito ,the best.

I'm originally from Chicago and relocated to Burlington to study at one of the local colleges. Upon my first semester in school, Red Square welcomed me to be a resident DJ at their venue - which later turned into two residencies per week. Red Square has always been there for me and helped me advance in my DJ passion and my efforts to be a professional marketer.

The Red Square environment is fun and exciting! As a DJ, I always see our guests enjoying themselves and having a memorable time. There are multiple stages in the venue that DJs and live bands perform on throughout the week. That being said, Red Square is the place to be for an array of music.
Great drinks & staff.  Always a good time!  Nothing better then a summer night having drinks on their patio and listening to music!!

I'm giving this 3 stars as bring a bit of an older couple it seemed more of a dive bar. they had live music which was fun, a lounge area and a dance and DJ area in the back. it seemed a little different than what we are used to and being a big beer drinker we stopped in for a drink. My fiance said the shock top didnt taste like normal and my ipa left a dry aftertaste in my mouth. so I'm not sure if I'd be returning. it was clean inside and friendly staff just not sure if it's a place for me.

WAY BIGGER THAN IT LOOKS! Step inside to a small dining like area and step up to the dance floor. A DJ room in the back corner and live music outside in the summer time. Only downside is the bathroom situation, (especially for gents apparently) but other than that, an awesome place to hang with friends.

What fun night life! We were in the area for a wedding and stopped in for late night drinks. The band you had was very entertaining and we ended up staying for a couple hours. Dancing, drinking, socializing...Thanks for the experience

Nicely built apartments. Stilt plus four. Ample free space , parking space and  good cross ventilation. Quite place away from the hustle and bustle yesterday just off the highway. Access is a bit round about , but since there is no traffic it's not an issue.

This place is good and calm. It is located on highway other side of mogappair & nolambur. While entering to Casagrand Cedars, we need to go through "Mass,rough,dirty" industries with short road. No hospitals / showrooms in this area.  For anything (except groceries), we need to cross highway and should go to mogappair.

Casagrand cedars is a residential apartments in Ayanambakkam. The flats here are of 2bhk and 3bhk. The cost are slightly affordable for a middle and higher middle class people. Amenities available. Parking is quite ok. Transit available.
Great apartment in the area. The best community in ayanambakkam
Too expensive for the location

Delicious food and excellent service! Tonight was our first experience eating Indian cuisine. Our waiter was knowledgeable and friendly with his recommendations and my husband and I both truly enjoyed our experiences.  We would recommend this restaurant to friends and family, and we will definitely be coming back ourselves.
This place was great. We ordered Lamb chops and chicken masala? (The first menu in curry categories) and they were nice. We will visit there again definitely.
The food is amazing and the wait staff so friendly. Every time we are in Ann Arbor we eat there as no other Indian restaurant is as good. We've been eating there for 20 years.

One of the best Indian restaurants I've eaten at and I have been eating there for years. Reminds me of the nicer Indian restaurants in Great Brittan where I first tried Indian food. Authentic food served in a very nice atmosphere. The waiters are all very professional and efficient. I asked about a dish I used to order but was not on the menu now and the waiter said they would make it for me... Chicken Hyderabadi (not sure I spelled that right) delicious! I'll back when I'm in town again.

The food is delicious in every word possible! I went with my mom, and she's usually picky when it comes to food, but she absolutely loved their food. Our waiter was the best! The prices are not that bad. The service was good, a man in a suit (I believe the owner) came to our to check up on us. All in all, it was a great first experience.
So comfortable.. and welcoming..cant do enough for you ..and very friendly
Welcoming host, generous provisions and close to all facilities but a little tired looking. Good value for money
